lines.text: I like what you're sayin', keep talkin'.
Mr. Booze! Mr. B-double-O-Z-E... don't ever choose!...
Be careful or six of your best friends will be carrying you by the handles.
You look like the day they fixed the electricity at the death house.

[referring to Marian]
Where did he dig that up?
Big Jim's daughter, there's a big laugh. I thought when you were a kid you didn't have a doll to play with, you had a rattle. It was right on the end of your tail.
